<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-68-0241 </DOCNO><TEXT>At many places in the British Isles, coal seams crop out on the surface.Given high amount of waste, the winning of coal became economical onlywith the application of modern and powerful machines. One of these open-castmines is the Roughcastle mine near Falkirk, Scotland, which has an averagewaste-to-coal ratio of 24:1. Since the end of 1986, the world's biggesthydraulic excavator, which has 500 t of service weight and was designedand constructed by Mannesmann-Demag, Duesseldorf, has been excavatingthis mine. Practical experience is reported. (orig./MOS)</TEXT></DOC>